[00:10.39]There is a pit beneath the holy ground
[00:15.00]where the fire waits, and the lost are found
[00:19.61]Yet never satisfied with endless death
[00:24.23]The worm lives deep within the depth
[00:28.84]It does not rest, it does not cease
[00:33.46]it chews forever never any peace
[00:38.07]Our tongues are split and crying out
[00:42.68]For drops that never fall
[00:47.30]We knew His name
[00:51.91]We knew His voice
[00:56.52]We chose not to call
[01:01.14]Where the worm does not die
[01:05.75]And the fire is never quenched
[01:10.36]gnashing of teeth of an empty cry
[01:14.98]Every second stretched
[01:19.59]No water given, no relief
[01:24.20]This is the end of borrowed breath
[01:28.82]And the forever heat
[01:33.43]No night, no dawn, no passing time
[01:38.05]Just smoke that rises, thick and slow
[01:42.66]The burning flesh doesn't pay the crime
[01:47.27]The distant light we will never know
[01:51.89]Every prayer we never meant
[01:56.50]Got us to this place we were sent
[02:01.11]We begged too late with broken words
[02:05.73]The thirst now never to heed
[02:10.34]The door was shut
[02:14.95]The sentence sealed
[02:19.57]Eternity agreed
[02:24.18]Where the worm does not die
[02:28.79]And the fire is never quenched
[02:33.41]The throat still burns, the soul still begs
[02:38.02]But mercy’s hand is clenched
[02:42.64]No finger dipped in cooling grace
[02:47.25]No Lazarus to plead our case
[02:51.86]Just endless sight of heaven’s edge
[02:56.48]Outer darkness
[03:01.09]Gnashing teeth
[03:05.70]Names sealed
[03:10.32]The book shut tight
[03:14.93]Smoke ascends forever night
[03:19.54]Where the worm does not die
[03:24.16]Where the fire never sleeps
[03:28.77]No rest for soul
[03:33.38]Tossed into the deep
[03:38.00]Thirst without a single drop
[03:42.61]Heat without a flame
[03:47.23]Judgment breathes and knows us all
[03:51.84]And calls us by name
[03:56.45]Water and light are just memories
[04:01.07]Only fire remains
[04:05.68]Souls burning in the flame
